    "description": {
      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 18</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 134</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><b>Cost</b> 6 gp <b>Weight</b> 1 lb.</p><p><b>Damage</b> 1d3 (small), 1d4 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x2; <b>Range</b> -; <b>Type</b> S; <b>Special</b> disarm or trip, monk</p><p><b>Category</b> Light; <b>Proficiency</b> Martial</p><p><b>Weapon Groups</b> Monk</p><h3>Description</h3><p>Forged in pairs, these solid metal blades end in curved hooks, while the hand guards are hammered into outward-facing spiked crescents. Both the crescent and the tip of the hilt are sharpened for combat. They can be wielded as single weapons or with two-weapon fighting styles. These weapons gain the disarm special feature when they are used individually. A pair of shang gou can also be formed into a single one-handed weapon to gain the trip special feature.</p>"
